<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="4" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[264,1323,767,1673]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
Diagnosis.­ 
<taxonomicName box="[408,593,767,792]" class="Insecta" family="Colobathristidae" genus="Trichocentrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ecuatorianus">
<emphasis box="[408,593,767,792]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">T. ecuatorianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be separated from all other species by the shape of the pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[396,487,807,833]" captionStart="FIGURES 18 ­ 20" captionStartId="6.[264,382,1824,1848]" captionTargetBox="[280,1310,905,1776]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[266,1321,889,1797]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 18 ­ 20: Head and thorax, lateral view. 18 ­ T. horvathi. 19 ­ T. vianai. 20 ­ T. ecuatorianus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/156365/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
Fig. 
<number box="[453,487,807,833]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="20.0">20</number>
</figureCitation>
). It is distinguished from 
<emphasis box="[799,969,807,832]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">T. amazonicus</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[1030,1206,807,832]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">T. guayanensis</emphasis>
by a yellowish macula on the anterior half of connexival segments four to seven.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[264,1323,767,1673]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
Description.­ Brachypterous. Length. 
<number box="[774,835,887,913]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="6.15" valueMax="6.3" valueMin="6.0">6­6.3</number>
(mean = 
<number box="[964,1005,887,913]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="6.2">6.2</number>
). General coloration light brown to dark brown, almost black.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[264,1323,767,1673]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
Head length 
<number box="[468,507,967,993]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="0.9">0.9</number>
­1.0 (mean = 
<number box="[673,728,967,993]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="0.93">0.93</number>
), width 
<number box="[829,941,967,993]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="1.12" valueMax="1.17" valueMin="1.07">1.07­1.17</number>
(mean = 
<number box="[1063,1117,967,993]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="1.11">1.11</number>
), interocular distance 
<number box="[332,445,1007,1033]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="0.595" valueMax="0.63" valueMin="0.56">0.56­0.63</number>
(mean = 
<number box="[555,611,1007,1033]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="0.58">0.58</number>
). Head black, abundantly tomentose except stridulatory area. Rostral length 
<number box="[439,552,1047,1073]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="1.085" valueMax="1.12" valueMin="1.05">1.05­1.12</number>
(mean = 
<number box="[668,723,1047,1073]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="1.09">1.09</number>
), extending just beyond bases of mesocoxae, ratio of segment lengths about 
<number box="[577,593,1087,1113]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="1.0">1</number>
: 
<number box="[610,666,1087,1113]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="0.76">0.76</number>
: 
<number box="[679,720,1087,1113]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="0.9">0.9</number>
: 
<number box="[734,773,1087,1113]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="1.1">1.1</number>
; light brown to brown, except segment I and apex of segment IV darker; with sparse, semierect hairs. Antenna elongate, light brown to brown, apex of segment III and segment IV darker; segment I with scattered, erect hairs, segments II to IV with abundant short, decumbent hairs, these more dense distally. Eyes reddish, protruberant.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[264,1323,767,1673]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
Pronotum convex (
<figureCitation box="[538,627,1287,1313]" captionStart="FIGURES 18 ­ 20" captionStartId="6.[264,382,1824,1848]" captionTargetBox="[280,1310,905,1776]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[266,1321,889,1797]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 18 ­ 20: Head and thorax, lateral view. 18 ­ T. horvathi. 19 ­ T. vianai. 20 ­ T. ecuatorianus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/156365/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
Fig. 
<number box="[594,627,1287,1313]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="20.0">20</number>
</figureCitation>
), dark brown, almost black; with sparse erect hairs; collar, anterior lobe laterally, and posterior lobe tomentose. In lateral view pronotum elevated (
<figureCitation box="[273,360,1367,1393]" captionStart="FIGURES 18 ­ 20" captionStartId="6.[264,382,1824,1848]" captionTargetBox="[280,1310,905,1776]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[266,1321,889,1797]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 18 ­ 20: Head and thorax, lateral view. 18 ­ T. horvathi. 19 ­ T. vianai. 20 ­ T. ecuatorianus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/156365/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
Fig. 
<number box="[327,360,1367,1393]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="20.0">20</number>
</figureCitation>
). Scutellum dark brown, almost black, tomentose; with large, erect spine, this yellowish, dark brown distally, with scattered erect hairs. Metanotum dark brown, almost black, tomentose. Hemelytra brachypterous, represented only by short wing pads. Pleura dark brown, almost black, except acetabular area of pro­ and mesocoxae light brown. Propleura tomentose, and meso­ and metapleura punctate. Legs light brown to brown; femora and tibiae with scattered erect hairs, these more dense on tibiae. Femora with small, scattered, dark brown spots, profemur with small spines internally and a large one distally.
</paragraph>
<caption pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<paragraph blockId="1.[264,1323,1726,1888]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[264,438,1726,1750]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">FIGURES 1­10</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName box="[453,618,1727,1750]" class="Insecta" family="Colobathristidae" genus="Trichocentrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ecuatorianus">
<emphasis box="[453,618,1727,1750]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">T. ecuatorianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, male and female genitalia. Male: 1­ last segment, posterior view. 2­ pygophore, dorsal view. 3­ pygophore, lateral view. 4­ left paramere, inner view. 5­ left paramere, outer view. 6­ endosomal sperm reservoir, posterior view. 7­ endosomal sperm reservoir, lateral view. Female: 8­ last segment, posterior view. 9­ last segment, lateral view. 10­ spermathecal bulb. Abbreviations: PR, proctiger region; VL, valvula; VLF, valvifer.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="3.[264,1324,284,950]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Abdomen brown to dark brown, with abundant short hairs on sterna II to VII. Connexival segments four to seven each with a yellowish macula externally on anterior half.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[264,1324,284,950]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[502,613,364,390]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 ­ 10" captionStartId="1.[264,382,1726,1750]" captionText="FIGURES 1 ­ 10: T. ecuatorianus, male and female genitalia. Male: 1 ­ last segment, posterior view. 2 ­ pygophore, dorsal view. 3 ­ pygophore, lateral view. 4 ­ left paramere, inner view. 5 ­ left paramere, outer view. 6 ­ endosomal sperm reservoir, posterior view. 7 ­ endosomal sperm reservoir, lateral view. Female: 8 ­ last segment, posterior view. 9 ­ last segment, lateral view. 10 ­ spermathecal bulb. Abbreviations: PR, proctiger region; VL, valvula; VLF, valvifer." pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Figs. 
<number box="[571,613,364,390]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="4.0" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="1.0">1­7</number>
</figureCitation>
): pygophore (
<figureCitation box="[782,853,364,390]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 ­ 10" captionStartId="1.[264,382,1726,1750]" captionText="FIGURES 1 ­ 10: T. ecuatorianus, male and female genitalia. Male: 1 ­ last segment, posterior view. 2 ­ pygophore, dorsal view. 3 ­ pygophore, lateral view. 4 ­ left paramere, inner view. 5 ­ left paramere, outer view. 6 ­ endosomal sperm reservoir, posterior view. 7 ­ endosomal sperm reservoir, lateral view. Female: 8 ­ last segment, posterior view. 9 ­ last segment, lateral view. 10 ­ spermathecal bulb. Abbreviations: PR, proctiger region; VL, valvula; VLF, valvifer." pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Fig. 
<number box="[840,853,364,390]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
) cup­shaped, visible in posterior view. The foramen (
<figureCitation box="[429,499,404,430]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 ­ 10" captionStartId="1.[264,382,1726,1750]" captionText="FIGURES 1 ­ 10: T. ecuatorianus, male and female genitalia. Male: 1 ­ last segment, posterior view. 2 ­ pygophore, dorsal view. 3 ­ pygophore, lateral view. 4 ­ left paramere, inner view. 5 ­ left paramere, outer view. 6 ­ endosomal sperm reservoir, posterior view. 7 ­ endosomal sperm reservoir, lateral view. Female: 8 ­ last segment, posterior view. 9 ­ last segment, lateral view. 10 ­ spermathecal bulb. Abbreviations: PR, proctiger region; VL, valvula; VLF, valvifer." pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Fig. 
<number box="[483,499,404,430]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
) dorsal and medial. Wall of pygophore posterior to foramen strikingly produced forming dorsally a hypandrium; parandria absent. Parameres (
<figureCitation box="[1121,1192,444,470]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 ­ 10" captionStartId="1.[264,382,1726,1750]" captionText="FIGURES 1 ­ 10: T. ecuatorianus, male and female genitalia. Male: 1 ­ last segment, posterior view. 2 ­ pygophore, dorsal view. 3 ­ pygophore, lateral view. 4 ­ left paramere, inner view. 5 ­ left paramere, outer view. 6 ­ endosomal sperm reservoir, posterior view. 7 ­ endosomal sperm reservoir, lateral view. Female: 8 ­ last segment, posterior view. 9 ­ last segment, lateral view. 10 ­ spermathecal bulb. Abbreviations: PR, proctiger region; VL, valvula; VLF, valvifer." pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Fig. 
<number box="[1177,1192,444,470]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
) in resting position situated outside the pygophore laterally, their axes diagonal to longitudinal axes of pygophore; shank (
<figureCitation box="[519,629,524,550]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 ­ 10" captionStartId="1.[264,382,1726,1750]" captionText="FIGURES 1 ­ 10: T. ecuatorianus, male and female genitalia. Male: 1 ­ last segment, posterior view. 2 ­ pygophore, dorsal view. 3 ­ pygophore, lateral view. 4 ­ left paramere, inner view. 5 ­ left paramere, outer view. 6 ­ endosomal sperm reservoir, posterior view. 7 ­ endosomal sperm reservoir, lateral view. Female: 8 ­ last segment, posterior view. 9 ­ last segment, lateral view. 10 ­ spermathecal bulb. Abbreviations: PR, proctiger region; VL, valvula; VLF, valvifer." pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Figs. 4, 5</figureCitation>
) subquadrate and robust, blade elongate, protuding basally, and setose over its surface. Endosomal sperm reservoir large, complex, strongly sclerotized, with large wings.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[264,1324,284,950]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Female genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[524,648,644,670]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 ­ 10" captionStartId="1.[264,382,1726,1750]" captionText="FIGURES 1 ­ 10: T. ecuatorianus, male and female genitalia. Male: 1 ­ last segment, posterior view. 2 ­ pygophore, dorsal view. 3 ­ pygophore, lateral view. 4 ­ left paramere, inner view. 5 ­ left paramere, outer view. 6 ­ endosomal sperm reservoir, posterior view. 7 ­ endosomal sperm reservoir, lateral view. Female: 8 ­ last segment, posterior view. 9 ­ last segment, lateral view. 10 ­ spermathecal bulb. Abbreviations: PR, proctiger region; VL, valvula; VLF, valvifer." pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Figs. 
<number box="[591,648,644,670]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="9.0" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="8.0">8­10</number>
</figureCitation>
): genital complex (
<figureCitation box="[876,988,644,670]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 ­ 10" captionStartId="1.[264,382,1726,1750]" captionText="FIGURES 1 ­ 10: T. ecuatorianus, male and female genitalia. Male: 1 ­ last segment, posterior view. 2 ­ pygophore, dorsal view. 3 ­ pygophore, lateral view. 4 ­ left paramere, inner view. 5 ­ left paramere, outer view. 6 ­ endosomal sperm reservoir, posterior view. 7 ­ endosomal sperm reservoir, lateral view. Female: 8 ­ last segment, posterior view. 9 ­ last segment, lateral view. 10 ­ spermathecal bulb. Abbreviations: PR, proctiger region; VL, valvula; VLF, valvifer." pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Figs. 8, 9</figureCitation>
) partially invaginated under segment VII. In posterior view, large valvula I and valvifer I visible and valvula II and valvifer II partially visible. Spermathecal bulb (
<figureCitation box="[822,907,724,750]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 ­ 10" captionStartId="1.[264,382,1726,1750]" captionText="FIGURES 1 ­ 10: T. ecuatorianus, male and female genitalia. Male: 1 ­ last segment, posterior view. 2 ­ pygophore, dorsal view. 3 ­ pygophore, lateral view. 4 ­ left paramere, inner view. 5 ­ left paramere, outer view. 6 ­ endosomal sperm reservoir, posterior view. 7 ­ endosomal sperm reservoir, lateral view. Female: 8 ­ last segment, posterior view. 9 ­ last segment, lateral view. 10 ­ spermathecal bulb. Abbreviations: PR, proctiger region; VL, valvula; VLF, valvifer." pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Fig. 
<number box="[877,907,724,750]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
) spherical, simple.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[264,1324,284,950]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
